   <head>EPIGRAM XII.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">WE thought you without titles great,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And wealthy with a small estate;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">While by your humble self alone,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">You seem unrated and unknown.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But now on fortune's swelling tide</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">High-borne, in all the pomp of pride;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Of grandeur vain and fond of pelf,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis plain, my lord, you knew yourself.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
